The paper deals with velocity estimation for driverless vehicles, which is a core problem in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves the use of a recurrent neural network, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of sensors and motor currents, which are related to control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper involves the use of advanced algorithms to solve a complex problem, which is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
